"lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業形態</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">講義</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業実施方法</div></td><td colspan=3 width="450" align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp&#9745対面&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744オンデマンド&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744同時双方向<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">ディプロマ・ポリシーとの対応</div><div style="margin:10px">&#9744&nbsp1.&nbsp人間、文化、社会の課題を技術的観点から理解・考察する能力<br>&#9745&nbsp2.&nbsp広い範囲の工学的知識と数理的理解<br>&#9744&nbsp3.&nbsp様々な研究者・技術者と意見を交わすことのできるコミュニケーション力<br>&#9745&nbsp4.&nbsp課題に対して適切なアプローチを計画し、解決する問題解決力<br>&#9745&nbsp5.&nbsp工学の高度な知識・技術とこれを現実課題に適用し解決する能力<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業の目的・達成目標</div><div style="margin:10px"><h4>In this course, you will …</h4>
<ul>
<li>Gain a greater awareness of the role of sound in information transfer</li>
<li>Hone your abilities to hear the sounds around you and consider the meaning of those sounds in your life</li>
<li>Think about sound defines the relationship of an individual and the community to the environment</li>
<li>Think about how sound is used in music and speech to create particular effects and types of communication</li>
<li>Consider how sounds are created</li>
<li>Learn how to use Volume, Pan, EQ, Compression to mix sound</li>
<li>Learn how to apply reverb, delay and other effects to create space within a mix</li>
<li>Combine sounds in different projects such as a radio show and a musical composition</li>
<li>Learn about accelerated learning techniques</li>
</ul>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>具体的な方法や計画はMoodleで説明を行うのでよく読むこと</p>
<ul>
<li>Week 1-3: Sound in the Environment</li>
<li>Week 4-8: <a href="https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/%22https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/%22https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/mod/resource/view.php?r=20325\&quot; data-mce-href="><span style="color: #000000;">Sound in Music</span></a></li>
<li>Week 9-11: <a href="https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/%22https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/%22https://pxycms.ict.nitech.ac.jp/mod/resource/view.php?r=20332\&quot; data-mce-href="><span style="color: #000000;">Sound in Language</span></a></li>
<li>Lesson 12-16: Education media</li>
</ul></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>You will be expected to make a lot of contributions to the class including many presentations. This course will primarily be in English. You will also be expected to research the content for these presentations yourself.</p>
<p>The grade for this course will be based on:</p>
<ul>
<li>Active participation in every class</li>
<li>Quality of research and presentations</li>
<li>Reports</li>
</ul></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>具体的な評価方法はMoodleで説明を行うのでよく読むこと</p>
<p>The grade (100%) will be based on the assignments you submit and the presentations that you make.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>This course will be carried out primarily in English. You may choose to submit your assignments and do your presentations in either language. Whichever language you choose, be sure to show that you have thought about the topic in detail and show evidence of this in your assignments and presentations.</p>
<p align="left">Preview: Preparation of learning materials (120 minutes)</p>
<p align="left">Review: Understand classroom lecture and explanations; and work on assigned tasks (reports, presentations, quizzes, etc.). (120 minutes)</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px"></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px"></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Questions can be sent by Moodle message.</p>
